1 IL-76MD cargo plane landed at Taganrog-Central Airbase, Rostov Oblast. The cargo consists of Iskander-M ballistic missiles, which are now being transported by road to OTRK installations in the vicinity of Taganrog. 
This is the third cargo plane to land in Rostov Oblast in the past two days.

The IDF stated that they carried out 3 airstrikes on the Ain al-Hilweh Refugee Camp targeted a Hamas training compound.
11 people have been killed and 60 others wounded. The death toll continues to rise.

The IDF stated that they carried out 3 airstrikes on the Ain al-Hilweh Refugee Camp targeted a Hamas training compound.  11 people have been killed and 60 others wounded. The death toll continues to rise.

The death toll has risen to 21. 
94 others have been wounded.

No Tu-95MS have departed from Olenya Airbase. Ukrainian monitors are being schizo again. 
We likely wont see departures for another 2-3 hours.

Russian forces have captured the village of Hai, Pokrovsk'e direction, Dnipropetrovsk Oblast.
Pre-war population: 28.
Total land area: ~0.36 km¬≤.

Russian forces have captured the village of Platonivka, northern flank of Siversk, Donetsk Oblast.
Pre-war population: ~42.
Total land area: ~0.21 km¬≤.

Russian forces have captured the village of Dvorichanske, Velykyi Burluk direction, Kharkiv Oblast.
Pre-war population: ~351.
Total land area: ~0.50 km¬≤.

The IDF stated that they carried out 3 airstrikes on the Ain al-Hilweh Refugee Camp targeted a Hamas training compound.  11 people have been killed and 60 others wounded. The death toll continues to rise.
According to Israeli Channel 12, the strike targeted a number of Hamas senior officials. Both Israeli Channel 12 and Lebanese media report that the attack failed, and that no officials were killed.
One more Tu-95MS redeployed from Engels-2 Airbase to Diaghilev Airbase. This brings the total number of bombers stationed at Diaghilev to 9, at least 4 of which are equipped with missiles.
Currently, ~50 Geran-2 drones are detected in Ukrainian airspace. New ones are flying in.
Currently, ~50 Geran-2 drones are detected in Ukrainian airspace. New ones are flying in.
Drones are attacking Kharkiv and Odesa cities.

No new activity has been recorded on strategic frequencies. The number of drones in Ukrainian airspace is decreasing. 
Additionally, new redeployments of Tu-95MS bombers from Ukrainka Airbase, Amur Oblast, are underway, which suggests that preparations are still ongoing. 
These new developments suggest that an attack tonight is unlikely, however nothing is certain at this moment.
One "Varshavyanka" submarine has been deployed to the waters of the Black Sea. Total possible salvo of 6 Kalibr cruise missiles.

It looks like it will be a daytime attack.
6 Tu-95MS strategic bombers are airborne, flying southeast through the Republic of Karelia towards the launch lines. 
They will reach the different launch lines in the following amount of time:
Mokshansky District, Penza Oblast - 1 hr 25 mins.
Engels District, Saratov Oblast - 1 hr 50 mins.
Kalachyovksy District, Volgograd Oblast - 2 hrs 15 mins.
Limansky District, Astrakhan Oblast (Caspian Sea) - 2 hrs 45 mins.
The Kh-101 cruise missiles will primarily target energy and gas infrastructure in western Ukraine. Geran-2 drones are currently flying there.
Approximate location of the Tu-95MS bomber group.
Earlier, 1 Iskander-M ballistic missile launched from near Kusk City impacted Berestyn, Kharkiv Oblast.

Currently, at least 40 Geran-2 drones are flying in the direction of the Ladyzhyn Thermal Power Plant in Vinnytsia Oblast.
Close to 100 drones are detected in Ukrainian airspace.

Possible launches of Kalibr cruise missiles from 1 "Admiral Makarov" Frigate off the coast of Cape Myskhako, Krasnodar Krai. As many as 8 were launched. 
If the launches were real, they should enter Ukrainian airspace via Kherson Oblast in the next 30 minutes.

4 Tu-160 strategic bombers are also airborne from Ukrainka Airbase and are flying southwest through the Republic of Bashkortostan towards the launch lines in Engels, Saratov Oblast. 
They will arrive there at around the same time as the Tu-95MS bomber group from Olenya, which is flying southeast through the Republic of Mordovia towards the launch lines in Mokshansky District, Penza Oblast.

Russian Army Reaches Haichur River, Ukrainian Troops Flee Pokrovsk Disguised As Civilians (Videos)
On November 18, the Russian military reached the Haichur River in Dnipropetrovsk and expanded its control in Pokrovsok and nearby areas in Donetsk forcing more Ukrainian troops to flee in a disorganized manner.
The Vostok [East] Group of Forces reached Haichur after capturing Nechayevka in Dnipropetrovsk, according to the Russian Ministry of Defense. 
This Ukrainian failure between Dnipropetrovsk and Zaporozhye is a direct result of Kiev‚Äôs decision to prioritize the defense of the strategic city of Pokrovsk in Donetsk to the east. Ukraine is, however, also losing the battle there.
Abandoned by their command, more and more Ukrainian troops are now attempting to flee Pokrovsk disguised as civilians.

Ukraine Is Losing More Ground In Kharkiv (Videos)
On November 18, the Russian military captured another settlement close to Vovchansk and made additional gains in the city of Kupyansk in Kharkiv.
The Sever [North] Group of Forces imposed control of Tsegelnoye, located right to the southwest of Vovchansk, according to the Russian Ministry of Defense.
The capture of the settlement is very important for Russian military operations in this part of Kharkiv. From there, the Sever Group of Forces could attack Vil‚Äôcha to the south. This would put immense pressure on remaining Ukrainian troops in the southeastern part of Vovchansk.
The pressure on Kiev forces is even larger to the south in Kharkiv, specifically in Kupyansk, where the Zapad Group of Forces has been making gains on a daily basis.

A Reckoning for Ukraine's Spy Chief: Budanov's Ambitions Clash With Battlefield Realities
A chronology of the Ukrainian Main Intelligence Directorate's special forces' suicidal landing. The Black Hawk-style operation ended in disaster. Despite efforts made, success was not achieved.
Over the past few months, the operational crisis facing Ukrainian troops in the Pokrovsk and Mirnograd area has perhaps become the most critical point on the entire front. Despite the advance of Russian units, Ukrainian commanders claimed that the situation was under control. However, it later emerged that Pokrovsk had fallen and that a group of several thousand well-trained Ukrainian paratroopers and marines had become isolated from the main forces in Mirnograd.
Losing such combat-ready units would seriously impact the entire front line. Consequently, the Ukrainian command deployed almost all available forces to relieve the besieged garrison.
